[2]
Date: Thu 12 May 2022 13:40 WIB
Source: CNBC Indonesia [in Indonesian, trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.cnbcindonesia.com/news/20220512123027-4-338461/ada-lockdown-ini-syarat-ri-dinyatakan-bebas-wabah-pmk


Director general of livestock and animal health, Nasrullah, has said that Indonesia had experienced several outbreaks of FMD, starting from the entry of FMD into Indonesia in 1887 in Malang, East Java which then spread to various regions, until the last outbreak on the island of Java in 1983 which started in East Java.

"With various efforts to control and overcome FMD, finally Indonesia succeeded in declaring FMD-free status in 1986 through Minister of Agriculture Decree, World Animal Health Organization (OIE) Number XI of 1990," said Nasrullah in his introduction, quoted on Thursday [12 May 2022]. Therefore, the declaration of FMD-free for Indonesia in accordance with the OIE provisions refers to the conditions for countries that have been declared free of FMD without vaccination. To get the recognition of FMD-free status, he continued, a formal report is required to the OIE, which explains in detail the program for eradication, surveillance, monitoring, animal health infrastructure, and the organization of the livestock industry.

