******
[3]
Date: Mon 16 May 2022 12:05 WIB
Source: CNN Indonesia [In Indonesian, trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.cnnindonesia.com/nasional/20220516112224-20-797179/yogyakarta-laporkan-dua-kasus-pmk-pertama


The Special Region of Yogyakarta (DIY) reported the first 2 cases of FMD. Cases were found in livestock in Galur District, Kulon Progo Regency. The head of the DIY Agriculture Service, Sugeng Purwanto, said the first 2 cases were found in a cow and a goat belonging to a local farmer. Both had suspected or indicated acute status since showing symptoms of being infected with FMD a few days ago.

"[In view of the suspicion], only in the form of caution, we have taken some concrete steps, directly coordinated by the Kulon Progo Regency Government with the police. Sugeng confirmed that the 2 animals have now been isolated or quarantined by a special task force. This includes disinfecting the cage where the cows and goats previously lived. Sugeng claims that, so far the findings of the FMD case in the DIY region have only been found in Kulon Progo. Other districts/cities [of Yogyakarta] still have no reports.

[The authorities] will continue to monitor the traffic of livestock shipments. This step, according to Sugeng, will still be the main focus of his staff. Especially considering the need for meat consumption in the DIY region, about 50 per cent of which is met from other regions.

Vehicles transporting livestock from red or black areas spreading FMD will be immediately asked to turn back by the checkpoint officer. Meanwhile, those arriving from the green area will still undergo inspection. The special task force team for anticipating FMD, continued Sugeng, will directly monitor animal markets as a step to prevent the possibility of being missed at the entrance to livestock traffic. "We still maintain conduciveness. We don't panic and so on, we remain vigilant," he concluded.

--
communicated by
ProMED

[The Special Region of Yogyakarta is a provincial-level autonomous region of Indonesia in southern Java. For the location of the Galur district within the Kulon Progo Regency, see map at https://goo.gl/maps/1fNLTwhEM33LrpgM9.

If the cases are confirmed, the Special Region of Yogyakarta will become Indonesia's 3rd province infected by FMD, and the 2nd on the island of Java. The provinces already reported officially as infected are Aceh (known as the northernmost and westernmost province-level division of Indonesia) on the island Sumatra, and East Java, on the island Java.

FMD virus may spread into uninfected regions by several means, including legal and/or illegal introduction of infected animals and/or their products, including meat, in particular bone-in meat.

Meat is imported to Indonesia from several countries, led by Australia, New Zealand, and India. India, in contrast to the other exporters, is an FMD-endemic country. India exported to Indonesia 76.3 million kg of meat with a transaction value of USD 263.5 million during 2020 (last year of which data are available; see https://www.cnnindonesia.com/ekonomi/20220513183814-92-796556/6-daftar-negara-asal-impor-daging-sapi-indonesia). - Mod.AS

